A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend an Act entitled "An Act to create a board of county commissioners for the county
2 of Jackson," approved December 18, 1901 (Ga. L. 1901, p. 257), as amended, particularly
3 by an Act approved March 16, 1999 (Ga. L. 1999, p. 3570), so as to revise provisions related
4 to filling certain vacancies on the board of commissioners; to provide for related matters; to
5 repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 An Act entitled "An Act to create a board of county commissioners for the county of
9 Jackson," approved December 18, 1901 (Ga. L. 1901, p. 257), as amended, particularly by
10 an Act approved March 16, 1999 (Ga. L. 1999, p. 3570), is amended by revising subsection
11 (b) of Section 5 as follows:
12 "(b)(1) In the event a vacancy occurs on the board of commissioners when at least 180
13 days remain in the unexpired term of office, the election superintendent of Jackson
14 County, within 15 days after the vacancy occurs, shall issue the call for a special election
15 to fill the vacancy for the remainder of the unexpired term. Such special election shall be
16 called and conducted as provided in Chapter 2 of Title 21 of the O.C.G.A., the 'Georgia
