17 Election Code,' as now or hereafter amended. Any person elected in a special election to
18 fill such a vacancy shall take office immediately upon certification of the results of such
19 special election and qualification. If such vacancy is in the office of chairperson of the
20 board of commissioners, the vice chairperson of the board shall exercise the powers and
21 duties of the chairperson for the period beginning on the date the vacancy occurs and
22 ending on the date the successor chairperson takes office for the remainder of the
23 unexpired term following the special election provided for in this subsection.
24 (2) Until such time as a permanent successor can be elected as provided for in
25 paragraph (1) of this subsection, the remaining members of the board of commissioners,
26 at their discretion, may appoint a qualified individual to temporarily fill any such
27 vacancy. Any such person appointed to temporarily fill a vacancy shall be appointed
28 using the same procedures as provided for in subsection (c) of this section."
29 SECTION 2.
30 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
